  - TOOL_CALL: prompt_generate_tool({"project_main_folder_path": "/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/binutils", "max_depth": 1, "config_folder_path": "/root/fix_build_agent/oss-fuzz/projects/binutils", "expert_knowledge": "**Expert Knowledge: Fuzzing Build Log Analysis for Binutils**\n\n**Error Pattern Identified:**\nThe build fails with linker error: `/usr/bin/ld: /src/binutils-gdb/zlib/libz.a: error adding symbols: file format not recognized`\n\n**Root Cause Analysis:**\n1. **File Format Mismatch**: The zlib static library (`libz.a`) has an incompatible file format for the AFL++ toolchain.\n2. **Compiler Toolchain Inconsistency**: The zlib library was likely built with the system compiler (gcc/clang) instead of the AFL++ compiler (`afl-clang-fast`).\n3. **Architecture/ABI Mismatch**: The library may have been built for a different architecture or with different compiler flags.\n\n**Common Causes and Solutions:**\n1. **Rebuild zlib with AFL++ compiler**: Ensure zlib is built using the same compiler toolchain as the main project.\n2. **Check zlib build configuration**: The zlib subdirectory in binutils may have its own build system that needs to be configured for AFL++.\n3. **Library path issues**: The linker may be picking up a pre-built library instead of rebuilding it.\n4. **Cross-compilation issues**: If the library was built for a different target, it won't be compatible.\n\n**Specific Observations from Build Log:**\n- The error occurs during linking of `size` binary: `CCLD size`\n- Later occurs during fuzzer linking: `clang++: error: linker command failed`\n- The zlib library path is: `/src/binutils-gdb/zlib/libz.a`\n- The build uses AFL++ compiler: `/src/aflplusplus/afl-clang-fast`\n\n**Recommended Investigation Steps:**\n1. Examine the zlib build process within binutils\n2. Check if zlib is being built with correct compiler flags\n3. Verify that `CC` and `CXX` environment variables are properly set for zlib build\n4. Consider rebuilding zlib separately with AFL++ toolchain\n5. Check for any pre-built zlib libraries that might be interfering\n\n**Pattern Recognition:**\nThis is a classic \"mixed toolchain\" problem where dependencies are built with different compilers than the main project. In fuzzing builds, all components must use the same fuzzing compiler (afl-clang-fast, afl-clang-fast++) to ensure binary compatibility."})
